data.text:
The short-lived democratic government in Japan fell after Tsuyoshi Inukai was assassinated on May 15, 1932.

Before his death, Inukai attempted to discuss the Manchurian problem with China which angered the military. Had he survived the attack, could he somewhat delay the war?
